place.name: MOONZIE
place.gazetteerText: Moonzie, par., N. Fife, on Moonzie Burn, 1258 ac., pop. 148; the church is 3 miles NW. of Cupar. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
